---
import Site from '../layouts/Site.astro';
---
<Site
  title="Consulting"
  description="Hands-on clinical research consulting — site start-up, inspection & audit readiness, SOP builds, data management, and AI-augmented operations. Scoped case-by-case, done by operators."
>
  <section class="prod-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/#products" class="prod-back">&larr; All products</a>
      <div class="section-label">Consulting</div>
      <h1>We don't advise. We do the work.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Site start-up, inspection prep, SOP builds, data cleanup, AI in your workflow &mdash; scoped case-by-case, done hands-on, not handed off in a deck.</p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="mailto:info@purpledirective.com?subject=Consulting%20%E2%80%94%20scoping%20call" class="btn-primary">Book a scoping call
          <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
        <a href="#services" class="btn-ghost">See what we do</a>
      </div>
      <div class="facts">
        <span class="fact">Case-by-case scope</span>
        <span class="fact">Hands-on, not slideware</span>
        <span class="fact">Clinical-research-native</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="services">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">What we do</div>
      <h2>Help where you're actually stuck.</h2>
      <p class="lede" style="max-width:46rem">Pick a service below, or just tell us where your site is stuck. We scope it tight &mdash; nothing you don't need &mdash; and the people who built the products do the work.</p>
      <div class="inst-grid">
        <div class="inst"><span class="ik">Site start-up</span><h3>Stand up a research site</h3><p>SOPs, regulatory binder &amp; TMF, essential documents, delegation log, and training &mdash; inspection-ready from day one.</p></div>
        <div class="inst"><span class="ik">Readiness</span><h3>Inspection &amp; audit readiness</h3><p>Mock audit and an ICH&nbsp;E6(R3) / 21&nbsp;CFR&nbsp;Part&nbsp;11 gap assessment, with a prioritized remediation punch-list.</p></div>
        <div class="inst"><span class="ik">Regulatory</span><h3>SOPs &amp; submissions</h3><p>Site-specific SOP development, plus IRB submission prep, amendments, and essential-document management.</p></div>
        <div class="inst"><span class="ik">Data</span><h3>Data management &amp; analytics</h3><p>CRF/EDC data cleaning and query management, enrollment and monitoring dashboards, and operational reporting.</p></div>
        <div class="inst"><span class="ik">On call</span><h3>Fractional regulatory / QA</h3><p>Ongoing regulatory and quality support &mdash; operators on call, without a full-time hire.</p></div>
        <a class="inst inst-wide" href="#ai"><span class="ik">AI-augmented &middot; new</span><h3>AI-augmented operations <span class="arr">&rarr;</span></h3><p>Assistants and automation for your team &mdash; SOP &amp; document Q&amp;A, intake triage, scheduling. Built on a HIPAA-eligible foundation under BAA, designed against 21&nbsp;CFR&nbsp;Part&nbsp;11, human-in-the-loop and fully logged.</p></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="ai" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="band-split">
        <div>
          <div class="section-label">AI-augmented operations</div>
          <h2>Put AI to work &mdash; responsibly.</h2>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p>We build AI assistants for the parts of your operation that drown in documents and routing: answering questions across your SOPs and binder, triaging intake, scheduling, and pre-screening on public criteria &mdash; with a person in the loop and every interaction logged.</p>
          <p>Anything that touches protected health information runs on a <b>HIPAA-eligible foundation under a Business Associate Agreement</b> and is <b>designed and tested against 21&nbsp;CFR&nbsp;Part&nbsp;11</b>. Anything that would speak to trial participants is deployed <b>only under IRB-approved protocols</b>. We scope each engagement to what's deliverable &mdash; and tell you plainly what isn't.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">How it works</div>
      <h2>Scope first. Then we get to work.</h2>
      <div class="feat-grid" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr)">
        <div class="feat"><h3>1 &middot; Scoping call</h3><p>We map your gap and tell you, honestly, what's deliverable and what isn't.</p></div>
        <div class="feat"><h3>2 &middot; Scoped proposal</h3><p>Clear deliverables, fixed scope, case-by-case &mdash; no open-ended retainers.</p></div>
        <div class="feat"><h3>3 &middot; Hands-on delivery</h3><p>Operators who have run studies do the work alongside your team.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proof" id="proof">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pl">How we work</span>
      <span class="pchip">Operators, not vendors</span>
      <span class="pchip">Designed against 21 CFR Part 11</span>
      <span class="pchip">Human-in-the-loop</span>
      <span class="pchip">Scoped, never open-ended</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-tail">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Let's scope it.</h2>
      <p>Tell us where your site is stuck. We'll tell you what we can do about it &mdash; and what we can't.</p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="mailto:info@purpledirective.com?subject=Consulting%20%E2%80%94%20scoping%20call" class="btn-primary">Book a scoping call</a>
        <a href="/#products" class="btn-ghost">Browse all products</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Site>
